810 if (UNLIKELY(callFrame->argumentCount() < 1))

830 if (UNLIKELY(callFrame->argumentCount() < 1))

1469JSC::IsoSubspace* JSInspectorFrontendHost::subspaceForImpl(JSC::VM& vm)
1470{
1471 auto& clientData = *static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
1472 auto& spaces = clientData.subspaces();
1473 if (auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForInspectorFrontendHost.get())
1474 return space;
1475 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSInspectorFrontendHost> || !JSInspectorFrontendHost::needsDestruction);
1476 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSInspectorFrontendHost>)
1477 spaces.m_subspaceForInspectorFrontendHost = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.destructibleObjectHeapCellType.get(), JSInspectorFrontendHost);
1478 else
1479 spaces.m_subspaceForInspectorFrontendHost = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.cellHeapCellType.get(), JSInspectorFrontendHost);
1480 auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForInspectorFrontendHost.get();
1481IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("unreachable-code")
1482IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("tautological-compare")
1483 void (*myVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSInspectorFrontendHost::visitOutputConstraints;
1484 void (*jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSC::JSCell::visitOutputConstraints;
1485 if (myVisitOutputConstraint != jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)
1486 clientData.outputConstraintSpaces().append(space);
1487IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1488IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1489 return space;
1490}

1492void JSInspectorFrontendHost::analyzeHeap(JSCell* cell, HeapAnalyzer& analyzer)
1493{
1494 auto* thisObject = jsCast<JSInspectorFrontendHost*>(cell);
1495 analyzer.setWrappedObjectForCell(cell, &thisObject->wrapped());
1496 if (thisObject->scriptExecutionContext())
1497 analyzer.setLabelForCell(cell, "url " + thisObject->scriptExecutionContext()->url().string());
1498 Base::analyzeHeap(cell, analyzer);
1499}

1516JSC::JSValue toJSNewlyCreated(JSC::JSGlobalObject*, JSDOMGlobalObject* globalObject, Ref<InspectorFrontendHost>&& impl)
1517{
1518 // If you hit this failure the interface definition has the ImplementationLacksVTable
1519 // attribute. You should remove that attribute. If the class has subclasses
1520 // that may be passed through this toJS() function you should use the SkipVTableValidation
1521 // attribute to InspectorFrontendHost.
1522 static_assert(!std::is_polymorphic<InspectorFrontendHost>::value, "InspectorFrontendHost is polymorphic but the IDL claims it is not");
1523 return createWrapper<InspectorFrontendHost>(globalObject, WTFMove(impl));
